HEADWORD: Jayhawker
<hw>Jay"hawk`er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A name given to a
free-booting, unenlisted, armed man or guerrilla.</def> <note>[A term of
opprobrium used in the war of 1861-65, U. S.]</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

